modules.description: This module provides a function to convert character streams into token streams, identifying keywords, identifiers, numbers, and strings. It works with character streams and custom token types, allowing specification of valid keywords. Concrete use cases include building lexers for programming languages or domain-specific parsers that require structured tokenization of input.

This module implements lazy streams and parsing operations for processing sequences of values. It supports creating streams from functions, lists, strings, bytes, and input channels, and provides functions to consume, inspect, and manipulate stream elements. Concrete use cases include parsing input from files, processing character streams incrementally, and implementing custom parsers that require lookahead or position tracking.
